(hours. Long-duration storage, pumped hydro, and other emerging options may play a larger) Tj
T*
(role over time, yet even modest battery deployment has already changed how planners think) Tj
T*
(about renewable integration.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Transmission is the less glamorous piece that often determines whether clean generation can) Tj
T*
(actually reach customers. Wind and solar resources are not always located near the cities) Tj
T*
(and industrial areas that consume the most electricity. A region may have excellent wind) Tj
T*
(potential but limited transmission capacity, which leads to congestion and delays. Building) Tj
T*
(new lines is slow because it crosses jurisdictions, property concerns, and environmental) Tj
T*
(review. As a result, some of the biggest bottlenecks in the energy transition are not about) Tj
T*
(generation technology. They are about moving electricity from where it can be produced) Tj
T*
(efficiently to where it is needed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The transition also affects jobs in uneven ways. Renewable energy creates work in) Tj
T*
(manufacturing, installation, electrical services, maintenance, and grid modernization. At) Tj
T*
(the same time, communities tied to coal mining, refining, or conventional power plants can) Tj
T*
(face real economic loss. A fair transition is not just a slogan. It requires retraining) Tj
T*
(pathways, local investment, and realistic planning for towns whose tax base and identity) Tj
T*
(were built around older energy industries. If policymakers ignore that human dimension,) Tj
T*
(resistance to change becomes much stronger and often understandable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Buildings and transportation are part of the same picture. Electrification shifts energy) Tj
T*
(demand from direct combustion toward the power grid. Heat pumps, electric vehicles, and) Tj
T*
(electric industrial processes can reduce emissions, but they also change when and how) Tj
T*
(electricity is used. Managed charging for vehicles, efficient appliances, and building) Tj
T*
(retrofits help ensure that electrification does not simply create new peaks that strain the) Tj
T*
(system. In that sense, clean power and efficient demand have to grow together. One without) Tj
T*
(the other makes the transition more expensive.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Local acceptance matters more than many planners first assume. Residents may support) Tj
T*
(renewable energy in principle but object to a specific project because of land use, visual) Tj
T*
(impact, wildlife concerns, or distrust of developers. That is why early community engagement) Tj
T*
(matters. Projects that communicate clearly about benefits, setbacks, timelines, and) Tj
T*
(environmental tradeoffs usually have a stronger chance of moving forward. Communities also) Tj
T*
